.TH LLAMA-GGUF-EMBED 1 "February 2026" "llama-gguf 0.5.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
llama-gguf-embed \- extract embeddings from text
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B llama-gguf embed
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
\fIMODEL\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Extract vector embeddings from input text using a GGUF model. Embeddings
can be used for semantic search, clustering, similarity comparison, and
other NLP tasks.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I MODEL
Path to the GGUF model file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-text " " \fITEXT\fR
Text to embed. Required.
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Default: json.
.RS
.IP \fBjson\fR
JSON object with text, dimension, and embedding array.
.IP \fBraw\fR
One value per line, suitable for piping to other tools.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
Extract embeddings in JSON format:
.PP
.RS
.B llama-gguf embed model.gguf --text "Hello, world!"
.RE
.PP
Extract embeddings in raw format:
.PP
.RS
.B llama-gguf embed model.gguf --text "Hello" --format raw
.RE
.PP
Save embeddings to file:
.PP
.RS
.B llama-gguf embed model.gguf --text "Sample text" > embedding.json
.RE
